    "note": "Single-source role map for the harness skills manifests (meta-spec owns the harness registry, so it owns the role registration too). generate-harness-skills-manifest.mjs reads this to fill the per-role skills.manifest.json skills[]. Every built skill resolves to exactly one role: assignments[name] when present, otherwise defaultRole. The three role sets partition the skills[] index (no skill in two roles). Skill names are plain strings; the specs-to-skills verify.mjs role-registration check cross-guards this index against the real skill folders on disk (an on-disk skill missing here is an orphan; a name here missing on disk is dead). defaultRole is worker, the scoped-execution majority (evaluators, node-/repo-/git- standards, single-schema graders); orchestrator is the coordinating/spawning contexts; user is the interactive surface that adds AskUserQuestion. Re-run byte-identical: no timestamp, no sha.",
